    • Method Detail

      • SetStock

        void SetStock​(Stock stock)
       throws DeliveryException,
              DryException
        Sets the stock the truck uses

        DryException is only thrown in OrdinaryTruck as no cold items can be stored in it.

        Parameters:
        stock - The stock used by the truck to contain items
        Throws:
        DeliveryException - thrown when truck's stock is over capacity
        DryException - thrown when a non-dry item is added to stock

      • getStock

        Stock getStock​()
        Returns the stock used by the truck
        Returns:
        The stock used by truck

      • getPrice

        double getPrice​()
        Returns the cost of using the truck

        Calculated based either the number of items in the trucks stock or the lowest temperature of the truck depending on whether the truck is refrigerated or ordinary.

        Returns:
        The price of using the truck

      • getCount

        int getCount​()
        Returns the total number of items in the truck
        Returns:
        The size of the stock in the truck

      • getTemperature

        double getTemperature​()
               throws DryException
        Returns the temperature set by the truck. Throws exception when used on Ordinary Truck
        Returns:
        The temperature of the truck
        Throws:
        DryException - Thrown when used on OrdinaryTruck has it has no temperature

      • IsFull

        boolean IsFull​()
        Returns true if the truck's stock is at capacity. Returns false if the truck is not at capacity.

      • toString

        java.lang.String toString​()
        Returns a string of the type of truck, the items in it's stock and their quantities.

        Expected string should be ">Refrigerated/Ordinary

        itemName1, itemQuantity1, itemName2, itemQuantity2, etc."

        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        A string of the truck's type and each item and item quantity in it's stock
